Kaduna and its environs on Saturday morning, remained peaceful, just as markets in various locations within Kaduna city remain scanty as Muslims in the state joined their counterparts around the globe to begin Ramadan. DAILY POST correspondent who went round the city on Saturday, observed the quietness and serenity of the environment. The Nigerian Supreme Council for Islamic Affairs (NSCIA), under the leadership of its President-General and Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Muhammad Sa’ad Abubakar III, had on Friday, announced the sighting of moon, showing the commencement of Ramadan this morning Saturday. However, DAILYPOST observed that there is a low turnout of market women and traders. Mohammed Abdul, at the Central market said, since today is the first day of the holy month of Ramadan, some of them will thoroughly observe it and prayerfully ask for God’s guidance. He said as a Muslims they are to fast, pray for their needs, the country and world. Also, Hajia Mariam Na’ Allah who sells foodstuff at Kakuri market said throughout this month, she will only open for business from 4pm, till down, as she will pray fervently. “I will not open my shop for business until 4pm, till the end of this month. ”By 4pm, I go to the shop to prepare food for breaking the fast.” Also it was observed that some shops, bus service, and other skeleton service providers are also observing the first day of the spiritual month, as their shops were locked, just as bus services that worked between 6am this morning were seen packed.